author: Written by: Chris Petrey
title: Police search for second suspect wanted in bike theft and shooti
text:
TERREBONNE PARISH, LA (WVUE) - Deputies in Terrebonne Parish are searching for a man accused in a bike theft and shooting.
His alleged partner turned himself in Monday morning.
Deputies are searching for 28-year-old Donald James.
James and 19-year-old Dequinn Jackson are accused of robbing a man at gunpoint on Aug. 16.
The sheriff's office say James and Jackson approached a man on a bicycle and demanded he give up the bike. When the bicyclist refused and attempted to flee, James allegedly shot him in the leg.
Jackson turned himself in and admitted to his role in the robbery on Monday, Oct. 19, according to deputies. Officers are still searching for James.
Warrants for James' arrest include simple robbery and possession of a firearm by a convicted felon. Anyone with information on James' whereabouts asked contact the Terrebonne Parish Sheriff's Office or CRIMESTOPPERS at 1-800-743-7433.
